reviews.review_text: raging opener!! The boys whipped us into a frenzy with that Jack Straw.  I remember it like it was yesterday!

Omni Daydream I went with a friend from Chicago, I do remember it like it was yesterday. The Weight was incredible & the band delivered. It was amazing seeing the Grateful Dead & actually lay eyes on the what everyone was following for all those years. Nobody can do it like the Grateful Dead.

great show a friend of mine did go to this show just a few months before I moved to ATL., he claimed he got a soundboard tape of the first set, it was amazingly clear. The J.Strw opener, is a real smoker, a solid, and clear Althea, real solid all the way thru first set, with a heartfelt, and maybe one of the best,'so many roads'....this definitely one of my favorite sets.

Strong show This is a decent, enjoyable aud and very worthwhile show that features an interesting well-integrated mix of old and new. Love the fiery Jack Straw to open the Spring '92 tour and you can feel the energy in the Omni rise accordingly as Jerry cranks it up; strong versions of So Many Roads and Picasso.... I REALLY like the St of Circum set 2 opener with super high energy -- really impressive, as is the Scarlet. #Worthy... and dont listen to the skeptics who say years like '92-'95 are worthless. Total B.S. If you just wanna 'pass through the show' crank up the Jack Straw and St of Circumstance and you'll end up wanting to hear more. Thx for taping and posting - -and of course thanks to the band.
